      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Our research team designs, builds, and tests the products and systems that go into every EES installation. Based at our purpose-built <a href="/laboratory/facility">research facility</a> in Moolap, Geelong, the team works across thermal comfort testing, product development, energy system integration, and field performance validation.
      </p>
      <p>
        This isn't theoretical research. Everything we develop gets tested in our full-scale TestCell under controlled, measurable conditions — then installed in real homes and buildings. The research team bridges the gap between lab testing and field performance.
      </p>

      <h2>What the Team Works On</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Thermal comfort testing</strong> — ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 compliant testing using calibrated comfort carts, heat flux meters, thermal imaging, and air velocity sensors</li>
        <li><strong>Hydronic ceiling panel development</strong> — designing, manufacturing, and testing our <a href="/laboratory/hydronic-ceiling-panels">radiant ceiling panels</a> for heating and cooling performance</li>
        <li><strong>Heat pump system optimisation</strong> — testing polyvalent heat pump configurations for maximum COP and simultaneous heating/cooling output</li>
        <li><strong>Environmental Service Pod (ESP)</strong> — developing and refining our <a href="/laboratory/environmental-service-pod">integrated modular energy system</a></li>
        <li><strong>Field performance monitoring</strong> — collecting and analysing long-term data from installed systems to validate lab results against real-world conditions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Research-Led Installation</h2>
      <p>
        What makes EES different from other installers is that our installation team and research team are the same company. The insights from testing directly inform how we design and install systems in homes and commercial buildings. When we say a system will perform a certain way, we have the test data to back it up.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our research has been documented in <a href="/laboratory/written-papers">published papers</a> and is available for review.
      </p>

